H3.text: In which Yorkshire town is the Harlow Carr RHS Gardens situated. HARROGATE

A4.text: RHS Harlow Carr gardens, on the western edge of Harrogate, are award-winning themed gardens and are the Royal Horticultural Society's main presence and representative in the North of England.

A5.text: Harlow Hill is a district to the west of the town, accessed by Otley Road. It has a number of new developments and an office park. It is known for RHS Harlow Carr Gardens.
